{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nThe reconciler constructs its Jira client inline at ~5 sites (each building an `AcliClient` /\ncalling the `_load_acli()` dynamic loader), so the vendor is chosen implicitly by which module\nis imported — there is no single place a second backend could be selected. This story adds a\nconfig key + an in-tree registry and a `select_backend()` entry point that returns the\n`Backend` facade from S2 [rebar:ce4d-c3ca-5412-4798], then routes those inline constructions\nthrough it. Behavior is unchanged: with the default config (`reconciler.backend = \"jira\"`),\n`select_backend()` returns a `JiraBackend` and every existing path behaves exactly as before.\n\nEdit-set:\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/config.py` (+ its schema) — add the\n  `reconciler.backend` key, default `\"jira\"`, validated against the registry's known keys.\n- New `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend_registry.py` — a `register(key, factory)`\n  decorator + `select_backend(config)` resolver (in-tree, import-time registration; no\n  entry-point plugins yet — YAGNI until a real external backend).\n- `adapters/jira/backend.py` — decorate `JiraBackend` with `@register(\"jira\", …)`.\n- The ~5 inline construction sites (per ADR §(a) leak list, e.g. `fetcher.py`, `applier.py`,\n  `run_differs.py`, and the `_load_acli()` callers) — replace the inline `AcliClient` build\n  with `select_backend(config)`.\n\n## Approach\n\nRegistry is a module-level dict populated by an idempotent `register` decorator, mirroring the\nin-tree decorator-registry pattern already used elsewhere in rebar (not a setuptools\nentry-point system — a second backend is added in-tree under `adapters/<x>/`). `select_backend`\nreads `config.reconciler.backend`, looks up the factory, and constructs the `Backend`; unknown\nkeys raise a config error listing registered keys. The 5 call sites change from \"build an\n`AcliClient`\" to \"ask the registry for the configured backend\"; each site keeps calling the\nsame transport/mapper methods, now via the `Backend` facade rather than a concrete client.\nTDD-held-out: registry-resolution + config-default + unknown-key tests authored RED first.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `reconciler.backend` config key + schema validation + default `\"jira\"`.\n- The registry module (`register` + `select_backend`) and `JiraBackend`'s registration.\n- Rewiring the ~5 inline `AcliClient`/`_load_acli()` sites to `select_backend(config)`.\n- **Out of scope:** the differ/apply field-mapping leak sites (S4 [rebar:6673-7636-a116-4f90]);\n  physically relocating vendor modules (S5 [rebar:dfb9-d2d1-455d-48d9]); the interface itself\n  (S2, prerequisite).\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Tier:** unit + integration, RED-first.\n- **Unit:** `select_backend` returns `JiraBackend` for the default config; raises a config\n  error naming registered keys for an unknown backend; the registry is idempotent under\n  repeated import.\n- **Integration/characterization:** a reconcile pass over a fixture store using the default\n  config produces the same events/outcome as pre-story `main` (proves the routing is\n  behavior-preserving through the real dispatch path, not just the resolver in isolation).\n- **Teeth:** point the config at a `FakeBackend` key and assert the pass drives the fake's\n  transport instead of Jira — confirming selection is actually honored end-to-end.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `config.reconciler.backend` exists, defaults to `\"jira\"`, and rejects an unregistered\n  value with an error listing the registered keys (verified by unit tests).\n- [ ] `select_backend(config)` returns a `Backend`; the default returns a `JiraBackend`\n  (verified by unit test).\n- [ ] All inline `AcliClient` constructions / `_load_acli()` calls at the rewired sites are\n  replaced by `select_backend(config)` — verified by `grep` showing no remaining inline\n  `AcliClient(` construction at those sites.\n- [ ] An end-to-end reconcile pass on the fixture store yields identical outcomes to pre-story\n  `main` under the default config (verified by the integration/characterization test).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784695742290087001,"uuid":"96e83901-9574-44af-b43d-434df41797a6"}